[{"sha":"43ebfab9af562fa7ea8eda4989aab339d3ded13d","author":{"email":"d4bfa6cff7deeb2d212f12b0b03668d8e8509321@google.com","name":"Anish Tondwalkar"},"message":"Add env var to eliminate op reorderings in TargetNodeReadyQueue

When the environment variable TF_DEREMINISTIC_ORDER=1 is set, TargetNodeReadyQueue will no no longer reorder ops. This eliminates reorderings due to ASLR in the TF executor, but op execution order remains nondeterministic due to multithreading and autotuning, when enabled.

We do this by reimposing a deterministic order on nodes in the ready queue. `node_id` s should now be deterministic (having been ordered based on node names set in the
GraphDef), but each node appears in multiple TargetNodes. We can identify which TargetNode we have for a given node by the properties of the innermost loop in which it reappears:
  - the frame of the loop at entry
  - the iteration number of that loop

This is encapsulated in a new Propagator for the graph executor, `OrderedPropagatorState` which derives from `PropagatorState`
